						               													<description>Welcome, researchers!&amp;#10; An unusually high amount of rare marine life has been spotted in a nearby cove. Whether you are an amateur or an expert diver, you cannot pass up the chance to research these amazing creatures. Make new discoveries to gain points, but don&amp;rsquo;t be naive, many of these creatures still pose a threat to those who wander too carelessly into their home!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     8 Amateur Diver Tokens&amp;#10;     8 Expert Tokens&amp;#10;     2 Dice&amp;#10;     16 Creature Cards&amp;#10;     1 Rules Card&amp;#10;     1 Research Vessel / Reference Card&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SETUP - Place the Research Vessel (RV) card to the side of the playing area. Spread the remaining cards face-down. Each player receives either the Red &amp;amp; Gold, or Blue &amp;amp; Silver set of diver tokens. Gold &amp;amp; Silver are experts, and let you adjust your dice roll by +/-1 on the turn they are added to a card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;ON YOUR TURN - The lowest dice roll goes first. Place 2 amateurs or 1 expert token on any face-down card (or face-up card that you control) per turn. Roll both dice. If either dice matches the back of the card, flip it and place your token on a free square. If the roll total matches any face-up cards with your diver on them, take the action shown and end your turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;DISCOVERIES - Each player may have a diver on a card back, however only the player who discovers it may add their tokens once the card flips. The losing player&amp;rsquo;s token is returned to them. If you place divers on all available spaces on a card, on your next turn you may take the card as a Discovery Point, and retrieve your divers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;INJURIES &amp;amp; ACCIDENTS - Dangerous creatures can injure your divers and send them to the RV. Once &amp;lsquo;healed&amp;rsquo; after 3 turns for injuries, or 1 for accidents, they can be placed again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HOW TO WIN - Collect 8 Discovery Points to win. Deduct 1 point for each diver still in recovery at the end of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
